headlines.description: — James Harden had 23 points and 16 assists, Norman Powell scored 26 of his 37 points in the second half and the Los Angeles Clippers overcame Nikola Jokic's 41 points to beat the Denver Nuggets 109-104 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harden, Powell help Clippers overcome Jokic's 41 points to beat Nuggets 109-104

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored six of his 37 points in the final 65 seconds and the Boston Celtics held on for a 124-118 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 37 points and Celtics hold to beat stubborn Pistons 124-118

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Chicago Bulls

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 23 points, Chet Holmgren added 21 points and a career-high 16 rebounds, and the Oklahoma City Thunder pounded Chicago 114-95 in the Bulls’ home opener on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander, Holmgren lead Thunder to easy win over Bulls, 114-95

headlines.description: — Santi Aldama scored 22 points, reserve center Jay Huff added a career-high 18 and the Memphis Grizzlies built a 26-point halftime team in a 124-111 victory over the Orlando Magic on Saturday night in their home opener.
headlines.shortLinkText: Aldama scores 22, Huff has career-high 18 as Grizzlies beat Magic 124-111 in home opener

headlines.description: — Julius Randle had 24 points nine rebounds and five assists and the Minnesota Timberwolves beat the Toronto Raptors 112-101 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Randle, Edwards each score 24 and Timberwolves top Raptors 112-101

events.name: Houston Rockets at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Victor Wembanyama scored 29 points, Jeremy Sochan added 17 points and 12 rebounds, and the San Antonio Spurs held on to beat the Houston Rockets 109-106 on Saturday night in their home opener.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wembanyama, Sochan help Spurs fend out hard-charging Rockets to win home opener, 109-106

events.name: Sacramento Kings at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James had a triple-double with 32 points, 14 rebounds and 10 assists, and Anthony Davis added 31 points and nine rebounds to lead the Los Angeles Lakers to a 131-127 victory over the Sacramento Kings on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron James records triple-double, Davis scores 31 in Lakers' 131-127 win over Kings
